devdoc.author: Fernando Malaspina
devdoc.details: Auction rules: - Bids must be at least 5% higher than the current highest bid. - The base price for the auction is 1 ether. - Auction duration is initially set to 7 days. - The auction is extended by 10 minutes with every valid new bid made in the last 10 minutes.   This allows other bidders enough time to respond.

params.lastBidder: Address of the bidder who triggered the extension.

params.winnerBid: Value of the winning bid in wei.

params.amount: Amount of the bid in wei.
params.bidder: Address of the wallet that placed the bid.

bid().details: Reverts if bid is not at least 5% higher or if sender is current highest bidder.

params._allowedIncrement: Allowed percent increment over the las bid.
params._extension: Auction extension when bid is placed within last 10 minutes.

returns._0: A list of BidRecord structs containing each bidder's data.
Bid containing the highest bidder and bid amount.

bidders.details: Helper array used to iterate over bidders for refund processing.

isRefunded.details: Is set to true when all balances had been refunded
